ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: a)  How has your interest in sex been over the past month?
Notes: 1=Greater than normal; 2=Normal; 3=Minimally diminished; 4=Moderately diminished; 5=Markedly diminished; 6=Totally absent

ElementDescription: b)  How has your ability to get sexually aroused or excited been over the past month?
Notes: 1=Greater than normal; 2=Normal; 3=Minimally diminished; 4=Moderately diminished; 5=Markedly diminished; 6=Totally absent

ElementDescription: c)  How has your ability to achieve orgasm been over the past month?
Notes: 1=Greater than normal; 2=Normal; 3=Minimally diminished; 4=Moderately diminished; 5=Markedly diminished; 6=Totally absent

ElementDescription: d)  (For men only) How has your ability to get and maintain an erection been over the past month?
Notes: 0=NA; 1=Greater than normal; 2=Normal; 3=Minimally diminished; 4=Moderately diminished; 5=Markedly diminished; 6=Totally absent

ElementDescription: e)  How would you rate your overall sexual satisfaction over the past month?
Notes: 1=Greater than normal; 2=Normal; 3=Minimally diminished; 4=Moderately diminished; 5=Markedly diminished; 6=Totally absent

ElementDescription: f)  How would you rate your overall improvement since your last medication change?
Notes: 0=NA; 1=Very much improved; 2=Much improved; 3=Minimally improved; 4=Unchanged; 5=Minimally worse; 6=Much worse

ElementDescription: Subject related information (e.g the affection, phenotype, disease information, etc.).
Study; The code for each individual study
